Cezanne: The Early Years, 1859-1872
Harry N. Abrams | 1988 | ISBN: 0810910489 | English | 248 pages | PDF | 31.7 MB

This new volume devoted to the early work of Paul Cezanne (1839-1906) is the first to explore the least-known period of this most brilliant, revolutionary, and influential of painters. His unique vision freed art from the academic constraints of the nineteenth century and heralded the beginnings of Cubism and the modern movement
